{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c2af588-df57-4dfe-bbce-6aa534fd9e8b","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter`** — run only the matching test.\n\nYou can also filter by shorter forms like:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nNow just edit your code/test and save — it'll re-run only that one test.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4e9b9bdf-fbd3-42ac-bade-babf67606e9e","outputTokens":155,"requestId":"0427:28DE61:1A578CE:1DE02EF:69E82586"},"id":"f8d9fbe3-cfc0-46a3-99ab-d9194bbef73d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:34:02.593Z","parentId":"630eead5-dc98-42b8-8ef8-44ca26b18bba"}
